    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-30T11:32:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-30T11:32:00-05:00" n="425"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-30T12:00:00-04:32"
                            >August 30, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. I am reliably informed that the military junta in Bolivia is negotiating with
                    the military junta in Peru for mutual recognition.<note n="8" xml:id="d425fn8"
                        >See “Revolution in Peru,” <ref target="frus1930v03#pg_720">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, pp. 720</ref> ff.</note> Bolivia hopes
                    thus to secure favorable modification of the terms of the treaty between Chile
                    and Peru.<note n="9" xml:id="d425fn9">See <ref target="frus1929v01#pg_720">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1929, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 720</ref> ff.</note> A member of the
                    junta or a confidential agent will probably leave for Lima early next week. The
                    Peruvian Chargé leaves for Lima Monday. He tells me he will endeavor to prevent
                    any modification of the treaty.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Lima.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
